 operator-configured\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\mcp.md:53:1. the MCP client spawns `openclaw mcp \r\nserve`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\mcp.md:314:- starts a second container that \r\nspawns `openclaw mcp serve`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\secrets.md:21:Recommended operator loop:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\security.md:29:This is for cooperative/shared \r\ninbox hardening. A single Gateway shared by mutually untrusted/adversarial operators is not a recommended setup; split \r\ntrust boundaries with separate gateways (or separate OS users/hosts).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\security.md:42:Settings prefixed with \r\n`dangerous`/`dangerously` are explicit break-glass operator overrides; enabling one is not, by itself, a security \r\nvulnerability report."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":926,"aggregated":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\acp.md:87:It spawns the ACP bridge and lets you \r\ntype prompts interactively.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\acp.md:92:# Point the spawned bridge at a remote \r\nGateway\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\acp.md:284:- `openclaw acp client` sets \r\n`OPENCLAW_SHELL=acp-client` on the spawned bridge process.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\devices.md:75:openclaw devices rotate --device \r\n<deviceId> --role operator --scope operator.read --scope operator.write\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\devices.md:100:- These commands require \r\n`operator.pairing` (or `operator.admin`) scope.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM